a list of some things i’ve been loving lately:

productive saturday’s. making lemonade. theo. chaturanga dandasana. adrien brody. moving my body. my morning routine. having a piano again. drinking coffee out by the river. the 1975. the barbie movie. siete salt and vinegar potato chips. friends. planning more trips. just the beauty of the world and life and being a girl!

💌🌞🍉🤍🥂🧸💐💫
tennessee is really starting to feel like home 🤎🌿🍂
we made it to ethiopia!! 🇪🇹 cheers to my brothers, new friends, and lots and lots of coffee
and we’ll do it all again in a week 🙌🏻
day two in addis has been so special! highlights include visiting entoto park, dancing & live music at a cultural dinner, and so much quality time with family & friends <3

we spent day three in gunchire and it’s been my favorite day so far! we started the day at the local kidmia center and had lunch & a coffee ceremony before meeting a few families that kidmia has helped empower. it was so inspiring to hear these families stories and how strong these mothers are. one of the women we met taught us how to make injera and it was such a special experience! a few of the kiddos around the village followed us and some of the girls were braiding my hair and holding my hands and it almost made me cry 🥹 we also had the privilege of meeting a few of the babies that are about to be adopted or reunited with family. we ended the night off with dinner at our lodge where we woke up to monkeys!! jude and i also got to walk around with our friend aschalew, who’s been a family friend for 12 years now and soak up some of his wisdom! truly so grateful for him, his encouragement, and everything he has been teaching me 🤍 so so grateful for this trip and everything the Lord has been doing
back in the states but missing ethiopia, the people, and the food so much <3
celebrating my 20th a couple days early while my grandparents are in town <3 backyard picnic with homemade cake, pizza, & sangria + ended the night out with a family game of croquet 🥂🎂🍂

love the weekends that i can get away from the noise and busyness & just be out in nature with the horses <3 homemade pizza nights, windowsill reading, kitten snuggles, dancing to italian music & sipping wine, bareback riding, & wearing the pink cowgirl hat from when i was a little girl. i love life 😊
quick trip to jupiter with daddicus 🌞🌊🌴

meet my new baby, blue jeans! 

kinda crazy how this whole thing came about but i am so incredibly grateful for answered prayers & supportive grandparents that helped work out the details that come with getting a horse. he’s the sweetest spotted saddle horse and he’s 12 years old. i’m obsessed with him.

fun fact! he looks so similar to my horse, lincoln, that i had when i was little 🥰 i’m a very happy girl!!
it’s been a sweet holiday season <3

2023 has been so so good to me <3 truly the best year of my life thus far & i have so much gratitude for every experience & person i met this year.

some highlights:
- adopting theo
- my first solo trip to italy & greece 
- becoming a yoga teacher
- moving into our new house
- ethiopia trip
- my 20th birthday
- adopting blue jeans
- saw ruel, gracie abrams, & the 1975 live
- new friends
- weekend trips to florida, montauk, arkansas 

hoping 2024 will be full of more relationship, learning, & traveling. happy new year <3
